<div class="container">
    <h1>8. Sibling Selectors</h1>

    <p>Sibling selectors are useful for targeting elements that share the same parent element. There are two main types: <strong>general sibling selectors</strong> and <strong>adjacent sibling selectors</strong>.</p>

    <h2>4.1 General Sibling Selector</h2>
    <p>The general sibling selector targets elements that share the same parent and appear after a specified element, using the tilde <code>~</code> character.</p>

    <div class="code-container">
        <div class="code-header">CSS</div>
        <div class="code-content">
            h2 ~ p { color: #333; font-size: 16px; }
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="code-container">
        <div class="code-header">HTML</div>
        <div class="code-content">
            &lt;p&gt;Not selected&lt;/p&gt;<br>
            &lt;section&gt;<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;p&gt;Not selected&lt;/p&gt;<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;h2&gt;Heading&lt;/h2&gt;<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;p&gt;This paragraph will be selected&lt;/p&gt;<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;div&gt;<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;p&gt;Not selected&lt;/p&gt;<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;p&gt;This paragraph will be selected&lt;/p&gt;<br>
            &lt;/section&gt;
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2>4.2 Adjacent Sibling Selector</h2>
    <p>The adjacent sibling selector targets elements that come directly after a specified element, using the plus <code>+</code> character.</p>

    <div class="code-container">
        <div class="code-header">CSS</div>
        <div class="code-content">
            h2 + p { color: #333; font-size: 16px; }
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="code-container">
        <div class="code-header">HTML</div>
        <div class="code-content">
            &lt;p&gt;Not selected&lt;/p&gt;<br>
            &lt;section&gt;<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;p&gt;Not selected&lt;/p&gt;<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;h2&gt;Heading&lt;/h2&gt;<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;p&gt;This paragraph will be selected&lt;/p&gt;<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;div&gt;<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;p&gt;Not selected&lt;/p&gt;<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;p&gt;Not selected&lt;/p&gt;<br>
            &lt;/section&gt;
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2>4.3 Sibling Selectors Example</h2>
    <div class="code-container">
        <div class="code-header">HTML + CSS</div>
        <div class="code-content">
            &lt;input type="checkbox" id="toggle"&gt;<br>
            &lt;label for="toggle"&gt;&#9776;&lt;/label&gt;<br>
            &lt;nav&gt;<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;ul&gt;<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;Home&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;About&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;Services&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;Contact&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;<br>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;/ul&gt;<br>
            &lt;/nav&gt;

            input { display: none; }<br>
            label, ul { border: 1px solid #cecfd5; border-radius: 6px; }<br>
            label { color: #0087cc; cursor: pointer; display: inline-block; font-size: 18px; padding: 5px 9px; transition: all .15s ease; }<br>
            label:hover { color: #ff7b29; }<br>
            input:checked + label { box-shadow: inset 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,.15); color: #9799a7; }<br>
            nav { max-height: 0; overflow: hidden; transition: all .15s ease; }<br>
            input:checked ~ nav { max-height: 500px; }<br>
            ul { list-style: none; margin: 8px 0 0 0; padding: 0; width: 100px; }<br>
            li { border-bottom: 1px solid #cecfd5; }<br>
            li:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }<br>
            a { color: #0087cc; display: block; padding: 6px 12px; text-decoration: none; }<br>
            a:hover { color: #ff7b29; }
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2>4.3.1 Sibling Selectors Overview</h2>
    <table class="selector-table">
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Example</th>
                <th>Selector Type</th>
                <th>Explanation</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>h2 ~ p</td>
                <td>General Sibling Selector</td>
                <td>Selects an element that follows anywhere after the prior element, with both elements sharing the same parent.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>h2 + p</td>
                <td>Adjacent Sibling Selector</td>
                <td>Selects an element that directly follows the prior element, with both elements sharing the same parent.</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>

